        "content": "<p>I’m reading TPIL and <a href=\"https://leanprover.github.io/theorem_proving_in_lean4/inductive_types.html\">Ch. 7</a> on inductive types has this simple example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Weekday</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">friday</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It also says that “The first character <code>|</code> in an inductive declaration is optional. We can also separate constructors using a comma instead of <code>|</code>.” But when I try these examples:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Weekday'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">friday</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">inductive</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Weekday''</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">friday</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>they fail to compile (regardless of the indentation I've tried). Am I misunderstanding that TPIL quote?</p>",
